Object.Field:
This is a rebuild of the original Organization_Main_map, without the usage of Reusable Mappings, and with the Journal information being leveraged at an intermediate point in the mapping's logical flow.
This mapping is in effectively a direct rebuild of the original Organization_Main_map, simply without Resuable Mappings, to rule out RMAPs being the cause of the journalized code generation error.
This rebuilt version still produces INVALID SQL upon generation in Incremental/Journalize mode for the I$ loading step.

This union operator provides a unique list of AN8 values appearing in either F0101_LT or F0116_LT. This allows us avoid direct joining of two journalized sources, but still identify only necessary journaled changes originating in either table.
DECODE( GREATEST(F0101_LT.ABUPMJ_ABUPMT_G, F0116_LT.ALUPMJ_ALUPMT_G), F0101_LT.ABUPMJ_ABUPMT_G, TRIM(F0101_LT.ABUSER), TRIM(F0116_LT.ALUSER) )
F0005_LT_SearchType.DRSY_T = '01' AND F0005_LT_SearchType.DRRT_T = 'ST' AND F0005_LT_SearchType.DRDL01_T != '.' AND TRIM(F0005_LT_SearchType.DRSPHD) != 'EXCLUDE'
